{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"48c39676-91a3-49d5-9b72-61f2b46a7ed7","content":"Since your project uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (via `global.json`), you can use the built-in hot reload flag:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis watches for file changes and automatically re-runs tests without a full rebuild. Much faster than `dotnet watch test`.\n\n---\n\nAs for the failing test — `RemoveStock` never throws. It just subtracts blindly. You need a guard in `RemoveStock`:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock.\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWant me to apply that fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9eec0b04-5151-44ce-ad70-6fdcd229edf0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for this test project. With .NET and the Microsoft Testing Platform (as configured in global.json), you can use `dotnet test --hotreload` or `dotnet watch test` to get hot reload for tests.\n\nLet me check what's available. Since this uses `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` as the test runner (from global.json), and MSTest 3.8.0, the recommended approach is `dotnet test --hotreload` which watches for file changes and re-runs tests automatically.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The options are:\n1. `dotnet watch test` - the classic approach using `dotnet watch`\n\n\n2. `dotnet test --hotreload` - the newer approach with Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\nSince they have `\"runner\": \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\"` in global.json, the `--hotreload` flag should be available with `dotnet test`. I'll recommend this approach and show them how to use it. I also noticed a potential bug where `RemoveStock` doesn't throw an exception when the quantity exceeds available stock.","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"9830:37E4CE:27E888:3482FB:69FFE1EB"},"id":"8696cd89-438e-4573-997e-0d96d5efbcbe","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:40:08.759Z","parentId":"ca073a74-3e8f-4a77-8df6-3aa223e34eee"}
